<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[341,499,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974 a) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974" yearSuffix="a">
Cook (
<number box="[420,478,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" value="1974.0">1974</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName box="[595,767,693,716]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[595,767,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1118,693,716]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[979,1118,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1134,1286,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" refString="Smith, I. M. (1976) A study of the systematics of the water mite family Pionidae (Prostigmata: Parasitengona). Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Canada, 98, 1 - 249." type="journal article" year="1976">
Smith (
<number box="[1219,1278,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" value="1976.0">1976</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
included the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[272,444,729,752]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,444,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his concept of 
<taxonomicName box="[652,791,729,752]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[652,791,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Pionacercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without discussing subgenera. Gerecke (
<number box="[1258,1317,728,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" value="2014.0">2014</number>
) proposed elevation of 
<taxonomicName box="[291,463,765,788]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[291,463,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to full generic rank. We follow that treatment here based on the apomorphic condition of the distal segments of the fourth leg in males and the unique configuration of the genital field in both sexes. The modifications to the distal segments of the fourth leg of males are similar to those found in males of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,286,871,896]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Madawaska" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,286,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Madawaska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above) suggesting that members of the two genera may be closely related. The phylogenetic affinities of 
<taxonomicName box="[286,458,909,932]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Pionacercopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[286,458,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Pionacercopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[521,656,908,933]" class="Arachnida" family="Pionidae" genus="Madawaska" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[521,656,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Madawaska</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other Foreliinae will be better understood when adults and larvae of additional species are described.
</paragraph>
